   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>8.1.1882 Sonntag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49096">Paris</placeName> January 8. 1882 Sunday</p>
            <p> Went to the <orgName key="80908">Gaite&#x2019;</orgName>
               <note type="reg">
                  <orgName key="80908">Théâtre de la Gaîté-Montparnasse</orgName>
               </note>, where they are
               acting &#x201e;<name type="work" key="28508">Quatre-vingt-treize</name>&#x201c;<note type="com">
                  <persName key="18866">Meurice</persName>
               </note>, with <persName key="537">Sophie</persName>. It is a war piece and there are
               some fine scenes in it, the best of which are when Gawain is comdemned to death and
               when he is beheaded. In coming home we were astonished to see a great crowd of
               &#x201e;badauds&#x201c; assembled on the boulevards before a watchmakers shop above whose door was
               painted a huge clock. In my astonishment and my inquisitiveness I went up to one of
               the gravest looking people of the crowd to find out the reason of it; he quite
               seriously answered that that clock, pointing to the one above the door, was going to
               change the colour of it&#x2019;s face. I laughed and went away! and this was the reason for
               a large crowd for I know the man told me the truth because everybody was talking and
               wondering what colour the clock would turn.</p>
         </div>
